value.value: A disorder characterized by the presence of blood in a fallopian tube.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate blood in the urine.
A finding based on laboratory test results that indicate increased levels of hemoglobin above normal.
A disorder characterized by a form of thrombotic microangiopathy with renal failure, hemolytic anemia, and severe thrombocytopenia.
A disorder characterized by bleeding from the hemorrhoids.

A disorder characterized by the inability of the liver to metabolize chemicals in the body. Laboratory test results reveal abnormal plasma levels of ammonia, bilirubin, lactic dehydrogenase, alkaline phosphatase, aminotransferase, and/or prolongation of prothrombin time (INR.) Drug-induced liever injury (DILI) as defined by Hy's Law.
A grouping of those organisms that are commonly used in laboratory research.
A disorder characterized by bleeding from the liver.
A disorder characterized by an infectious process involving the liver.
A disorder characterized by a sensation of marked discomfort in the liver region.
A disorder characterized by a viral pathologic process involving the liver parenchyma.
A disorder characterized by repeated gulp sounds that result from an involuntary opening and closing of the glottis. This is attributed to a spasm of the diaphragm.
A finding of traumatic injury to the hip in which the continuity of either the femoral head, femoral neck, intertrochanteric or subtrochanteric regions is broken.

A disorder characterized by the presence of excess hair growth in women in anatomic sites where growth is considered to be a secondary male characteristic and under androgen control (beard, moustache, chest, abdomen).
A disorder characterized by harsh and raspy voice arising from or spreading to the larynx.
A disorder characterized by an uncomfortable and temporary sensation of intense body warmth, flushing, sometimes accompanied by sweating upon cooling.

Infectious agents, which while normally present but remaining benign under the control of the immune system, become virulent and pathogenic in immune-compromised hosts (i.e when they get the opportunity to become infectious).
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate an elevation in the concentration of calcium (corrected for albumin) in blood.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate an elevation in the concentration of blood sugar. It is usually an indication of diabetes mellitus or glucose intolerance.
A disorder characterized by excessive sweating.

A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate an elevation in the concentration of potassium in the blood; associated with kidney failure or sometimes with the use of diuretic drugs.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate an elevation in the concentration of magnesium in the blood.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate an elevation in the concentration of sodium in the blood.
A disorder characterized by an increase in production of parathyroid hormone by the parathyroid glands. This results in hypercalcemia (abnormally high levels of calcium in the blood).
A disorder characterized by characterized by excessive sleepiness during the daytime.
A disorder characterized by excessive levels of thyroid hormone in the body. Common causes include an overactive thyroid gland or thyroid hormone overdose.
A disorder characterized by hair density or length beyond the accepted limits of normal in a particular body region, for a particular age or race.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate an elevation in the concentration of triglyceride concentration in the blood.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate an elevation in the concentration of uric acid.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate a low concentration of albumin in the blood.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate a low concentration of calcium (corrected for albumin) in the blood.
A disorder characterized by dysfunction of the hypoglossal nerve (twelfth cranial nerve).
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate a low concentration of glucose in the blood.
A disorder characterized by reduced sweating.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate a low concentration of potassium in the blood.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate a low concentration of magnesium in the blood.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate a low concentration of sodium in the blood.
A disorder characterized by a decrease in production of parathyroid hormone by the parathyroid glands.
A disorder characterized by laboratory test results that indicate a low concentration of phosphates in the blood.
A disorder characterized by a decrease in production of thyroid hormone by the thyroid gland.
A disorder characterized by a narrowing of the lumen of the ileum.
Taxonomic family which includes rabbits and hares.

value.value: A disorder characterized by an infectious process involving the skeletal muscles.
A disorder characterized by adverse reaction to the infusion of pharmacological or biological substances.
